---

<Main>
  <Section class="space-y-6">
    <p>
      Graduated <a
        href="https://wikipedia.org/wiki/National_University_of_Singapore"
        >NUS</a
      > in Dec 2025. Now holds a math degree (2<sup>nd</sup> Major CS btw), and is
      looking for a job (cf. <a
        href="https://github.com/nguyenvukhang/site/releases/download/v1/resume.pdf"
        >resume</a
      >). Helped TA for <a href="https://nusmods.com/courses/CS2030/">CS2030</a> and
      <a href="https://nusmods.com/courses/CS2040/">CS2040</a>.
    </p>

    <p>Sleeps, codes, climbs, runs, learns cryptography.</p>

    <p>
      Life goal is to make fast, reliable, and secure software so that people
      can enjoy modern software without needing modern hardware.
    </p>

    <p>
      Keeps a <a href="/articles">small blog</a>, and a <a href="/links"
        >list of cool websites</a
      >.
    </p>

    <p>
      Does projects to solve daily-life problems and learn code in an applied
      setting:
    </p>

    <div class="mb-6 space-y-text">
      <Project name="Gitnu" href="https://github.com/nguyenvukhang/gitnu/">
        <div slot="summary">Enumerates git status</div>
        <div slot="description">
          {c.GITNU_DOWNLOADS} downloads on <a
            href="https://crates.io/crates/gitnu">crates.io</a
          >
        </div>
      </Project>

      <Project name="Pass" href="https://github.com/nguyenvukhang/pass/">
        <div slot="summary">Single-file password store</div>
        <div slot="description">GnuPG keyring + ChaCha20</div>
      </Project>

      <Project name="Statc" href="https://github.com/nguyenvukhang/statc/">
        <div slot="summary">
          Convenience routines for statistics calculations
        </div>
        <div slot="description">
          {c.STATC_DOWNLOADS} downloads on <a
            href="https://crates.io/crates/statc">crates.io</a
          >
        </div>
      </Project>

      <Project name="Wordle" href="https://github.com/nguyenvukhang/wordle/">
        <div slot="summary">A fun application of Information Theory</div>
        <div slot="description">Evaluates wordle algorithms in &lt;2s</div>
      </Project>
    </div>

    <p>Explores other languages to keep an open perspective:</p>

    <div class="mb-6 space-y-text">
      <Project name="Helium" href="https://github.com/nguyenvukhang/helium/">
        <div slot="summary">
          Wacom Tablet Driver extension for Precision Mode
        </div>
        <div slot="description">
          Swift, XCode, macOS UI Application; also in daemon form
        </div>
      </Project>
      <Project
        name="Canvas Sync"
        href="https://github.com/nguyenvukhang/canvas-sync/"
      >
        <div slot="summary">Cross-platform GUI synchronization tool</div>
        <div slot="description">
          C++, Qt6 Framework, automated builds on GitHub
        </div>
      </Project>
      <Project
        name="Aquarium"
        href="https://github.com/nguyenvukhang/aquarium/"
      >
        <div slot="summary">
          Backtracking solver for the <a href="https://puzzle-aquarium.com/"
            >Aquarium</a
          > puzzle
        </div>
        <div slot="description">Implemented in both Swift and Rust</div>
      </Project>
      <Project
        name="Nvim Toggler"
        href="https://github.com/nguyenvukhang/nvim-toggler/"
      >
        <div slot="summary">Toggle words under your cursor</div>
        <div slot="description">
          Lua plugin for Neovim, {c.NVIM_TOGGLER_STARS}â˜… on GH, featured in <a
            href="https://github.com/coffebar/dotfiles">coffeebar/dotfiles</a
          >
        </div>
      </Project>
    </div>
    <p>
      Find me on <a href="https://github.com/nguyenvukhang/">GitHub</a>,
      <a href="http://linkedin.com/in/nguyenvukhang/">LinkedIn</a>, and <a
        href="https://instagram.com/chalk.hang/">Instagram</a
      >. And if you're hiring, here's <a
        href="https://github.com/nguyenvukhang/site/releases/download/v1/resume.pdf"
        >my resume</a
      >.
    </p>
  </Section>
</Main>

<!-- styles -->
<style>
  @reference "../styles/global.css"
  p {
    @apply mb-6;
  }
  p > b {
    @apply font-semibold;
  }
</style>
